author: Kat Bein
title: Milo Yiannopoulos: Twitter Goes Nuts Over Ex-Breitbart Editor's Dubstep Logo | Billboard
text:
COMMENTS Drew Angerer/Getty Images Milo Yiannopoulos announces his resignation from Brietbart News during a press conference on Feb. 21, 2017 in New York City. 
Former Breitbart senior editor Milo Yiannopoulos is making headlines today (Feb. 22) after his resignation from the right-wing publication. A video surfaced that showed Yiannopoulos made comments defending acts of pedophilia, and he says he stepped down in order to remove his own wrong doings from the conversation about Breitbart as a whole. 
If only that were the only unfortunate thing in Yiannopoulos' life. Turns out he's got a real wicked personal logo as well. His resignation memo showed that black-and-white, angular monstrosity to the world, and Twitter is having quite a time poking fun at its expense. It does look like a cliché dubstep or metal logo, and some people find even more harrowing visuals hidden inside. Check it out for yourself. All that's left of Milo is his discount Skrillex logo pic.twitter.com/bOI56fy3jN — John Hendrickson (@JohnGHendy) February 21, 2017 milo's logo is fully within the zone of "local DJ who exclusively works in boregore remixes" pic.twitter.com/LyovRzsG24 — ▲ Catecorgi III ▲ (@corgzone) February 21, 2017 why does milo's logo look like the first person on a human centipede pic.twitter.com/WUH7tLBgMj — Mollie Goodfellow (@hansmollman) February 21, 2017 Not even kidding, when I was 18 I was in a band that did Cream, Free and Zeppelin covers called Milo as this was pretty much our logo pic.twitter.com/IReYylFYiR — Adim Hales (@adimhales) February 22, 2017 sorry but i’ve used angles to decipher the true spirit of the milo logo & it’s good actually pic.twitter.com/h9OYdrNGKs
